the skiing is varied, above and below the treeline and always with wonderful scenery all around.the monte rosa region is firmly on the "must ski" list for advanced skiers because of its big verticals and spectacular off piste descents.there is no nursery provision for younger children and, depending on the number and age mix of participants, even the youngest children may be out in mixed-groups with adults.it is therefore well worth signing up for a guided tour or for ski touring expeditions.the gressoney valley contains several different village bases and it is worthwhile checking which one accommodation offered is in and how that location relates to the ski lift network.in terms of on-piste terrain, intermediates will enjoy monte rosa the most, with more than 40 red (intermediate) graded runs to choose from covering about three quarters of the groomed trails.heli-boarding is an option the well-heeled and technically able will wish to take advantage of from the resort.although it is not on the scale of the famous french three valleys, it is a big area with nearly 200km (125 miles) of piste spread across varied terrain.excursions to the vallee blanche, the world's longest off piste descent above chamonix and courmayeur are offered.advanced+ the monte rosa region is firmly on the "must ski" list for advanced skiers because of its big verticals and spectacular off piste descents.the largest village in the area is gressoney st jean which is lower down at 1387m. it is not directly connected to the main ski areas, although it does have a small ski area of its own.the ancient language and customs are maintained by local associations and reflected in museums and cultural events.gressoney itself has descents nearing the world's biggest, with vertical descents approaching 2000 metres possible.- snowboarding at gressoney+ there are no terrain parks in the area and the main attraction, as for better skiers, is the extensive freeriding terrain.ski holidays in gressoney suitable for families+ there is not a great deal especially designed for children in the gressoney valley, although the area's strong community values, friendly people and establishments and beautiful setting all make it a pleasant place for a family ski trip.